msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.156:0.2"
msgid "16. Nandikkhayavagga "
msgstr "16. The End of Relishing "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 156. Ajjhattanandikkhayasutta → ajjhattanandikkhayaaniccasuttaṃ (bj) | nandikkhaya 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.156:0.3"
msgid "156. Ajjhattanandikkhayasutta "
msgstr "156. The Interior and the End of Relishing "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.142, sc1
#. VAR: sāssa → sāyaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.156:1.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhuṃ aniccanti passati, sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, the eye really is impermanent. A mendicant sees that it is impermanent: that’s their right view. "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.2"
msgid "Sammā passaṃ nibbindati. "
msgstr "Seeing rightly, they grow disillusioned. "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.3"
msgid "Nandikkhayā rāgakkhayo; "
msgstr "When relishing ends, greed ends. When greed ends, relishing ends. "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.4"
msgid "rāgakkhayā nandikkhayo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.5"
msgid "Nandirāgakkhayā cittaṃ suvimuttanti vuccati … pe … "
msgstr "When relishing and greed end, the mind is said to be well freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.156:1.6"
msgid "aniccaṃyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jivhaṃ aniccanti passati, sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi. "
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.7"
msgid "Sammā passaṃ nibbindati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.8"
msgid "Nandikkhayā rāgakkhayo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.9"
msgid "rāgakkhayā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.10"
msgid "cittaṃ suvimuttanti vuccati … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.11"
msgid "aniccaṃyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu manaṃ aniccanti passati, sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi. "
msgstr "mind really is impermanent. A mendicant sees that it is impermanent: that’s their right view. "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.12"
msgid "Sammā passaṃ nibbindati. "
msgstr "Seeing rightly, they grow disillusioned. "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.13"
msgid "Nandikkhayā rāgakkhayo; "
msgstr "When relishing ends, greed ends. When greed ends, relishing ends. "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.14"
msgid "rāgakkhayā nandikkhayo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.156:1.15"
msgid "Nandirāgakkhayā cittaṃ suvimuttanti vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "When relishing and greed end, the mind is said to be well freed.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.156:1.16"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

